<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#00ff00">Originally posted by k7 on 01-18-2001 03:45 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">So, now an abusive father has killed his son, and it's being blamed on everquest.  Even though he may not have even been playing the game at the time, and even though there is sufficient downtime to do many things, including cooking a meal, and tending to a child, even a caulic child (caulic babies cry a LOT).

This is just more material for the people that say "D&D is evil and will make kids go crzy and get suicidal."

Heck, I wouldn't be surprised if this story was mde up by one of those people.

If it really did happen, it was not because of EQ.  It was because he had issues.  Maybe he was beaten to near death when he was a child.  He just wasn't ready for a child, but had one anyway, and instead of dealing with it properly, he allowed it to anger him.  A caulic baby can be frustrating, and some people just can't handle it.  Some people can't even handle a healthy baby.

If he was so engrossed in EQ he wouldn't have even heard the crying.  If EQ was in any way at fault the child would have probably starved or suffocated to death.  Sometimes I hear the answering machine without hearing the phone ring, because I am so lost in the game and don't want to talk on the phone.

I say the news article was a lie, or at least imbued with the poor reporting skills of a tabloid.

Edit:  Just read the original article.

Surprise surprise, it was done by "the times".  Isn't that set of news papers notorious for poor reporting and non-existant research skills?

You should see some of the lousy articles that arrive on people's doorsteps with the name "&lt;yourcity&gt; Times" on the cover.

Might as well get a tabloid.

[This message has been edited by k7 (edited 01-18-2001).]</TEXTAREA>
